# Committed `cargo vendor` tree (reproducible-builds-musl cycle, P3b) — store
# EVERY vendored file VERBATIM, byte-for-byte. `cargo vendor` writes a
# `.cargo-checksum.json` per crate carrying the SHA-256 of each file's ORIGINAL
# bytes; the `--locked --offline` reproducible build verifies those checksums.
# git's default text/eol handling would CRLF→LF-normalize the vendored files
# that ship with CRLF (e.g. `vendor/zerocopy/win-cargo.bat`) on commit, mutating
# their bytes out from under the committed checksum → a clean checkout would fail
# the offline build with a checksum mismatch. `-text` disables all EOL
# normalization + binary/text detection for the vendor tree so the committed
# bytes match what `cargo vendor` emitted (and what the checksums pin). ms has no
# `* text=auto` rule today, but this guard is mandatory the moment one is added.
vendor/** -text
